{
  "image": "6518\\6518.jpg",
  "title": "Bomb",
  "description": "Dora Award winning director Lianna Makuch helms the Canadian premiere of Bomb by Ukrainian playwright Natalia Blok, featuring a star-studded cast (Rachel Bowron, Brett Dahl, Mariya Khomutova, and James MacDonald). Explosively funny and razor sharp, Bomb is a dark absurdist comedy that detonates with wit and strikes deep.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Natalia Blok<br><strong>Director</strong>: Lianna Makuch<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Rachel Bowron, Brett Dahl, Mariya Khomutova, James MacDonald<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Stephanie Bahniuk (Production), Bernardo Pacheco (Sound)<br/><strong>Stage Manager</strong>: Lore Green | PRODUCER Sheiny Satanove<br/></br>",
  "website": "https://pyreticproductions.ca | @pyretic.theatre",
  "plain_language": "Bomb is a dark comedy about Dasha, a Ukrainian activist whose brain won’t shut up. The year is 2017. Dasha is trying to save the world, fix her relationship, and get her therapist to stop asking questions she doesn’t want to answer. It’s not going well. Her thoughts are spiraling, her reality is bending, and every conversation feels like a small explosion. As the pressure builds, Dasha starts to unravel... Bomb is fast, funny, darkly absurd, and a little bit tragic. It’s about burnout, big emotions, and staying sane when the world feels like it’s blowing up.",
